segments.text: Before I begin, may I ask the holder of paddle 187 to go back to the paddle registration desk?
And in order to encourage you to do so, you'd let your credit card there.
It's a great pleasure for us to offer this evening and continuing tomorrow with the collection of the Garden Limited, a collection of books and manuscripts.
We not only have a credit card, we have this lexicon.
Everything is sold to you subject to the conditions of sale and the terms of guarantee which appear in the front part of the catalog.
And I call your attention to the 10% buyer's premium payable on all purchases, and I remind you that any sales taxes which apply applies the full purchase price, which includes the buyer's premium.
All lots of this sale noted in your catalog, sir, payment will be due to subsidies and will not be accepted prior to January 3, 1990.
No lots will be released to a price of prior payment on January 3, 1990, unless special credit arrangements concerning the lotto may be directly with other institutions.
And that's only for a phone member or somebody to talk to you about that.
The auctioneer may open bidding on any lot by placing a bid on behalf of the seller by placing successful consecutive bids or by placing bids in response to other bidders.
And to start this evening with block number one, shown here, shown to you on the wall in front.
